-- Soldier Field in Chicago Evacuated Because of Threat of Tornado
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2013-11-17T18:58:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-17/soldier-field-in-chicago-evacuated-because-of-threat-of-tornado.html
Soldier Field  in Chicago was
evacuated after play between the Bears and Baltimore Ravens was
suspended because of the threat of a tornado in the area.  The National Football League game was stopped with the
Ravens leading 10-0 with less than five minutes to play in the
first quarter.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  